reviewText: Anything by Part deserves high ratings. The reason for four stars is the presence of Wilson and his choreography. May be okay (I was not a fan) but juxtaposed to Arvo's sublime music, it just seemed silly.
Arvo Part rarely ventures out in public. And this is a great DVD - "In The Lost Paradise" - we can really follow him over a period of one year in his native Estonia, to Japan and the Vatican.
Arvo Prt... A living legend. A humble man...
